      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>

        <h3>Getting Started</h3>
        <h4>How do I create an account?</h4>
        <p>
          Visit <a href="https://app.equiduty.se">https://app.equiduty.se</a> and click "Get Started" or
          "Sign Up". Enter your email address and create a password. You can also sign in with Google.
        </p>

        <h4>How do I invite members to my stable?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Log in to your account<br/>
          2. Go to Settings → Members<br/>
          3. Click "Invite Member"<br/>
          4. Enter the member's email address and select role (Stable Owner, Guest)<br/>
          5. Click "Send Invitation"
        </p>

        <h4>Which plan fits my stable?</h4>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> 1-5 users, basic features, perfect for small stables</li>
          <li><strong>Premium S:</strong> 6-10 users, advanced features, small to medium stables</li>
          <li><strong>Premium M:</strong> 11-25 users, priority support, medium stables</li>
          <li><strong>Premium L:</strong> 26-100 users, enterprise features, large stables</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          See full feature comparison on our <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a>.
        </p>

        <h3>Account and Billing</h3>
        <h4>How do I reset my password?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Go to <a href="https://app.equiduty.se">https://app.equiduty.se</a><br/>
          2. Click "Forgot Password?"<br/>
          3. Enter your email address<br/>
          4. Check your email for reset link<br/>
          5. Follow instructions to create a new password
        </p>

        <h4>How do I upgrade my subscription?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Log in to your account<br/>
          2. Go to Settings → Subscription<br/>
          3. Select the plan you want to upgrade to<br/>
          4. Confirm payment method<br/>
          5. Upgrade takes effect immediately
        </p>

        <h4>How do I cancel my subscription?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Log in to your account<br/>
          2. Go to Settings → Subscription<br/>
          3. Click "Cancel Subscription"<br/>
          4. Confirm cancellation<br/>
          5. You retain access to paid features until the end of your billing period
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Note:</strong> Monthly fees are non-refundable. Annual subscriptions can be refunded within
          14 days per Swedish law.
        </p>

        <h4>How do I export my data?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Log in to your account<br/>
          2. Go to Settings → Data and Privacy<br/>
          3. Click "Export Data"<br/>
          4. Select which data to export (horses, schedules, horse health records)<br/>
          5. Click "Start Export"<br/>
          6. You'll receive an email with download link (JSON format)
        </p>

        <h4>How do I delete my account?</h4>
        <p>
          1. Export your data first (see above)<br/>
          2. Go to Settings → Data and Privacy<br/>
          3. Click "Delete Account"<br/>
          4. Confirm deletion (this cannot be undone)<br/>
          5. Your account and all data are permanently deleted within 30 days
        </p>

        <h3>Technical Issues</h3>
        <h4>I can't log in</h4>
        <p>
          Common solutions:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Check that you're using the correct email and password</li>
          <li>Use "Forgot Password?" to reset</li>
          <li>Clear browser cache and cookies</li>
          <li>Try a different browser or incognito mode</li>
          <li>Check that your email is verified (check spam folder)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If the problem persists, contact <a href="mailto:info@equiduty.se">info@equiduty.se</a> with details.
        </p>

        <h4>The app doesn't work on my phone</h4>
        <p>
          Troubleshooting steps:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>iOS:</strong> Requires iOS 15.0 or later. Update to latest iOS version.</li>
          <li><strong>Android:</strong> Requires Android 8.0 or later. Update to latest Android version.</li>
          <li>Restart the app</li>
          <li>Check your internet connection</li>
          <li>Update app to latest version from App Store/Google Play</li>
          <li>Clear app cache in device settings</li>
          <li>Uninstall and reinstall the app</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>My notifications aren't working</h4>
        <p>
          Check:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Notifications are enabled in Settings → Notifications</li>
          <li>Notifications are allowed on your device (iOS: Settings → Notifications → EquiDuty, Android: Settings → Apps → EquiDuty → Notifications)</li>
          <li>Email notifications aren't going to spam</li>
          <li>Your email address is correct in account settings</li>
          <li>For Telegram: Bot is correctly configured with /start</li>
        </ul>

        <h4>I can't upload photos</h4>
        <p>
          Common causes and solutions:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>File Size:</strong> Maximum file size is 10 MB per photo. Compress larger images.</li>
          <li><strong>File Format:</strong> Accepted formats: JPG, PNG, HEIC/HEIF. Convert other formats.</li>
          <li><strong>Internet Connection:</strong> Check that you have stable connection during upload.</li>
          <li><strong>Permissions:</strong> Give app access to camera/photo library in device settings.</li>
          <li><strong>Storage Space:</strong> Check that you haven't reached your plan's storage limit.</li>
        </ul>
